parameters: \n<\c[14]Percy\c>Darn! Still no sign of \c[1]Oberon\c. I really hope he’s okay. I’ll search every inch of this place if
I have to, this sweltering heat won’t stop me from finding him.
\n<\c[14]Percy\c>Hmm, that’s weird. I didn’t expect to discover the totem just sitting here. Where is the thief?
\n<\c[14]Percy\c>Oh, thank goodness, you’re alright! How did you get away from your captor?
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>That I am, well, other than my poor singed beard! Er …
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>I … incapacitated him before making my escape, which involved getting a little too close to
\n<\c[14]Percy\c>Well, I can’t do anything about your beard, but I do have the \c[10]Fire totem.
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>Oh, Splendid work, \c[14]Percy\c! You have really come through for me.
\n<\c[14]Percy\c>It’s weird though, I just found it laying here. I thought the thief would have it, and
I’d have to battle them for it.
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>It’s a stroke of good luck! You know what they say about looking a gift horse in the mouth.
\n<\c[14]Percy\c>I came from over there. I definitely didn’t see you or the thief and I left no stone unturned.
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>Oh, fine, you’ve got me… there is no thief.
\n<\c[14]Percy\c>What!?!? If there’s no thief, then how did the totems get displaced?
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>I didn’t try taking them if that’s what you're thinking.
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>Uh … I may have accidentally knocked one off the altar, it doesn’t matter how, just
\n<\c[14]Percy\c>I wish you would’ve just told me what really happened when I first got here. I would’ve
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>Oh, \c[14]Percy\c, you are certainly one of the kindest sprites I have ever met, and it is a
privelege and an honour to call you my friend.
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>One thing that this whole situation has made clear is that it is time for me to find
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>Will you succeed me as \c[27]Elysian’s\c new protector?
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>You’ve shown me you’re more than ready.
\n<\c[1]Oberon\c>Wonderful! I know Elysian will be safe in your capable hands.
